# Additional Terms (Section 7 of AGPL-3.0)

## Section 7 - Additional Terms

### 7.1 Application of Additional Terms

The following additional terms apply to your use, reproduction, and
distribution of the Program:

a) **Source Code Availability**: Any network use of this Program must
   provide recipients access to the complete Corresponding Source of the
   Program as defined by AGPL-3.0 Section 1.

b) **Attribution**: All copies of the Program and derivative works must
   retain the original copyright notice, this license text, and the
   notice that the Program is licensed under the GNU Affero General
   Public License.

c) **No Trademark Rights**: This license does not grant permission to
   use the trade names, trademarks, service marks, or product names of
   the licensor, except as required for reasonable and customary use in
   describing the origin of the Program.

## Section 13 - Network Use

For the avoidance of doubt, Section 13 of the GNU Affero General Public
License (remote network interaction) applies. If you modify the Program
or a derivative work thereof and convey the modified version to users
over a network:

a) You must offer access to the Corresponding Source of the modified
   version from a network server at no charge.

b) You must inform users that the Corresponding Source is available at
   no charge.

c) You must keep the Corresponding Source available for as long as you
   offer the modified version over the network.

